   Did Lincoln Say, ‘If You Want to Test a Man’s Character, Give Him
   Power’?

Did Lincoln Say, ‘If You Want to Test a Man’s Character, Give Him Power’?

     * 25 September 2019
     * Fact Check

   For nearly a century, people have made the mistake of claiming that a
   quotation about Lincoln was actually a quotation by him.

   Woman Behind French #MeToo Movement is Fined for Defamation

Woman Behind French #MeToo Movement is Fined for Defamation

     * 25 September 2019
     * AP News

   A Paris court ruled that she must pay $22,000 for defaming the man she
   accused of harassment.

   Oklahoma Army Base Memo Warns of Potential Theater Threat

Oklahoma Army Base Memo Warns of Potential Theater Threat

     * 25 September 2019
     * AP News

   A document prepared at a U.S. Army base in Oklahoma says officials have
   been alerted to "disturbing" online chatter about a potential mass
   shooting threat at a theater during next week's release of the movie
   "Joker," but it references no specific location.

   Is Greta Thunberg the ‘Highest Paid Activist’?

Is Greta Thunberg the ‘Highest Paid Activist’?

     * 25 September 2019
     * Fact Check

   Detractors have been searching for an ulterior motive behind teenager
   Greta Thunberg's climate activism.

   Lawyers for Trump Try to Block Subpoena for His Tax Returns

Lawyers for Trump Try to Block Subpoena for His Tax Returns

     * 25 September 2019
     * AP News

   Lawyers for President Donald Trump and Manhattan District Attorney
   Cyrus R. Vance Jr. are facing off in court in a fight over the
   president's tax returns, and his claim to be immune from any criminal
   investigation as long as he is in the White House.

   ‘We’re All in Big Trouble’: Climate Panel Sees a Dire Future

‘We’re All in Big Trouble’: Climate Panel Sees a Dire Future

     * 25 September 2019
     * AP News

   Earth is in more hot water than ever before, and so are we, an expert
   United Nations climate panel warned in a grim new report.

   New Burial Rules Seek to Extend Arlington Cemetery Lifespan

New Burial Rules Seek to Extend Arlington Cemetery Lifespan

     * 25 September 2019
     * AP News

   The Army is proposing new rules to significantly restrict eligibility
   for burial at Arlington National Cemetery, seeking to preserve a
   dwindling number of gravesites well into the future.

   Memo: Trump Prodded Ukraine Leader on Biden Claims

Memo: Trump Prodded Ukraine Leader on Biden Claims

     * 25 September 2019
     * AP News

   President Donald Trump repeatedly prodded Ukraine’s new leader to work
   with Rudy Giuliani and the U.S. attorney general to investigate
   Democratic political rival Joe Biden, according to a rough transcript
   summarizing the call.

   Voracious Swamp Rodents Set Off Alarms in California

Voracious Swamp Rodents Set Off Alarms in California

     * 25 September 2019
     * AP News

   One of the most recent threats to California's environment has webbed
   feet, white whiskers, shaggy fur and orange buck teeth that could be
   mistaken for carrots.

   Jann Wenner to Retire as Rock and Roll Hall of Fame Chairman

Jann Wenner to Retire as Rock and Roll Hall of Fame Chairman

     * 25 September 2019
     * AP News

   The co-founder and publisher of Rolling Stone magazine is one of the
   founding members of the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame and is credited with
   recruiting the late architect I.M. Pei to create its Cleveland museum.

   New Climate Report: Oceans Rising Faster, Ice Melting More

New Climate Report: Oceans Rising Faster, Ice Melting More

     * 25 September 2019
     * AP News

   Due to climate change, the world's oceans are getting warmer, rising
   higher, losing oxygen and becoming more acidic at an ever-faster pace
   and melting even more ice and snow, a grim international science
   assessment concludes.

   Deported Army Veteran Returns to US in Bid to Become Citizen

Deported Army Veteran Returns to US in Bid to Become Citizen

     * 25 September 2019
     * AP News

   Federal immigration authorities granted Miguel Perez Jr. a two-week
   parole into the U.S. for an immigration hearing.

